{"author":{"id":"75732e82453cc4795a3b5d7bef7a9ce916b428e5bbe06161843f7392657be5c1"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1449745172,"nonce":"Ku4MCsGLKFvtqLXwi+K3wE+G+nI=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWUxMjE0NTg2MDU=","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/477","origin":"github"},"title":"ncurses 5.9 fails to compile (gcc \u003e 5.1)","message":"On my local instance installation of package_r_edger_3_11_0 fails because compilation of package_ncurses_5_9 fails with the following error:\n\n```\nSTDERR\nIn file included from ../ncurses/curses.priv.h:283:0,\n                 from ../ncurses/lib_gen.c:19:\n_4238.c:835:15: error: expected ‘)’ before ‘int’\n../include/curses.h:1594:56: note: in definition of macro ‘mouse_trafo’\n #define mouse_trafo(y,x,to_screen) wmouse_trafo(stdscr,y,x,to_screen)\n                                                        ^\nmake[1]: *** [../obj_s/lib_gen.o] Error 1\nmake: *** [all] Error 2\n```\n\nIt seems to be a GCC \u003e5.1 specific issue: https://github.com/cloudius-systems/osv/issues/634\n\nThis is the third issue caused by specific versions of GCC. (https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/466 and https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/pull/306 / https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/304 )\nI know we have a C/GCC compiler as requirement for installation, but maybe it's time to consider to have a C/C++ compiler, gcc or clang, as a tool dependency in iuc?\n\nTo solve the issue for edgeR, could I upgrade the R version from 3.1.2 to 3.2.1 (depending on ncursus 6.0 which is not affected) or may this break test cases?","files":null}]}